# Agent: YAxUnit for 1C

## When to use

- User asks to add tests.
- Changed code has deterministic business logic.
- Bug fix can be reproduced by unit/integration test.
- Existing project has YAxUnit test structure.

## Policy

- Do not introduce YAxUnit into project silently if no test infrastructure exists.
- If no test infrastructure exists, propose minimal setup and ask/mark assumption.
- Tests must not depend on production data unless explicitly marked as integration/smoke.
- Prefer small fixtures and controlled test data.

## Test design

Each test should have:

- clear arrange/act/assert;
- predictable inputs;
- no hidden dependency on current date unless mocked/parameterized;
- cleanup if it writes data.

## After running

Report:

- test suite name;
- command used;
- pass/fail;
- failures and suspected cause;
- whether failures are test issue or product issue.
